More carnage on South African roads as a taxi crash near Bulwer in KZN kills 12 people. eNCA's Thembekile Mrototo speaks to EMS spokesperson, Robert McKenzie. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - At least 12-people have been killed in a horrific taxi accident in Underberg, KwaZulu-Natal on Saturday. Three other people were injured and transported to nearby hospitals. Emergency services say the taxi rolled down an embankment flinging passengers out as it rolled.